    "bbox": [
      67.89,
      125.95,
      543.39,
      254.81
    ],
    "text": "Although the final ground of appeal urged by the counsel for the Appellant has some merit it has not caused any substantial miscarriage of justice as the prosecution has presented cogent evidence to prove the case for the prosecution beyond reasonable doubt and the misdirection on the part of the Learned High Court Judge is curable under proviso to Section 334(1) of the Code of Criminal Procedure Act.",
    "fonts": [
      "Times-Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      15.949620246887207,
